e": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "user", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "types", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "statuses", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "handlers", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "limit", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "offset", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "sort", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "currentUser", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "parentJob", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["List a page of jobs for a given user.\n\n```\nparam user\n\nThe user who owns the job.\n\ntype user\n\ndict, 'all', 'none', or None.\n\nparam types\n\njob type filter.\n\ntype types\n\narray of type string, or None.\n\nparam statuses\n\njob status filter.\n\ntype statuses\n\narray of status integer, or None.\n\nparam handlers\n\njob handler filter.\n\ntype handlers\n\narray of type string or None, or None.\n\nparam limit\n\nThe page limit.\n\nparam limit\n\nThe page limit.\n\nparam offset\n\nThe page offset.\n\nparam sort\n\nThe sort field.\n\nparam parentJob\n\nParent Job.\n\nparam currentUser\n\nUser for access filtering.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "girder_jobs.models.job.Job.findWithPermissions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "query", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "offset", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "limit", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "timeout", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "fields", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "sort", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "user", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "level", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "types", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "statuses", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "handlers", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "jobUser", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "parentJob", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Search the list of jobs.\n\\:param query: The search query (see general MongoDB docs for \"find()\")\n\\:type query: dict\n\\:param offset: The offset into the results\n\\:type offset: int\n\\:param limit: Maximum number of documents to return\n\\:type limit: int\n\\:param timeout: Cursor timeout in ms. Default is no timeout.\n\\:type timeout: int\n\\:param fields: A mask for filtering result documents by key, or None to return the full\n\n> document, passed to MongoDB find() as the `projection` param.\n\n```\ntype fields\n\n.\n\nparam sort\n\nThe sort order.\n\ntype sort\n\nList of (key, order) tuples.\n\nparam user\n\nThe user to check policies against.\n\ntype user\n\ndict or None\n\nparam level\n\nThe access level.  Explicitly passing None skips doing\npermissions checks.\n\ntype level\n\nAccessType\n\nparam types\n\njob type filter.\n\ntype types\n\narray of type string, or None.\n\nparam statuses\n\njob status filter.\n\ntype statuses\n\narray of status integer, or None.\n\nparam handlers\n\njob handler filter.\n\ntype handlers\n\narray of type string or None, or None.\n\nparam jobUser\n\nThe user who owns the job.\n\ntype jobUser\n\ndict, 'all', 'none', or None.\n\nparam parentJob\n\nParent Job.\n\nreturns\n\nA pymongo Cursor or CommandCursor.  If a CommandCursor, it\nhas been augmented with a count function.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "girder_jobs.models.job.Job.cancelJob", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "job", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Revoke/cancel a job. This simply triggers the jobs.cancel event and\nsets the job status to CANCELED. If one of the event handlers\ncalls preventDefault() on the event, this job will *not* be put into\nthe CANCELED state.\n\n```\nparam job\n\nThe job to cancel.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "girder_jobs.models.job.Job.createLocalJob", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "module", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "function", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Takes the same keyword arguments as {py:func}`createJob`, except this\nsets the handler to the local handler and takes additional parameters\nto specify the module and function that should be run.\n\n```\nparam module\n\nThe name of the python module to run.\n\ntype module\n\nstr\n\nparam function\n\nFunction name within the module to run. If not passed,\nthe default name of \"run\" will be used.\n\ntype function\n\nstr or None\n\nreturns\n\nThe job that was created.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "girder_jobs.models.job.Job.createJob", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "title", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "type", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "args", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "kwargs", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "user", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "when", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "interval", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "public", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "handler", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "asynchronous", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "save", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "parentJob", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "otherFields", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create a new job record.\n\n```\nparam title\n\nThe title of the job.\n\ntype title\n\nstr\n\nparam type\n\nThe type of the job.\n\ntype type\n\nstr\n\nparam args\n\nPositional args of the job payload.\n\ntype args\n\nlist or tuple\n\nparam kwargs\n\nKeyword arguments of the job payload.\n\ntype kwargs\n\ndict\n\nparam user\n\nThe user creating the job.\n\ntype user\n\ndict or None\n\nparam when\n\nMinimum start time for the job (UTC).\n\ntype when\n\ndatetime\n\nparam interval\n\nIf this job should be recurring, set this to a value\nin seconds representing how often it should occur. Set to <= 0 for\njobs that should only be run once.\n\ntype interval\n\nint\n\nparam public\n\nPublic read access flag.\n\ntype public\n\nbool\n\nparam handler\n\nIf this job should be handled by a specific handler,\nuse this field to store that information.\n\nparam externalToken\n\nIf an external token was created for updating this\n```\n\njob, pass it in and it will have the job-specific scope set.\n\\:type externalToken: token (dict) or None.\n\\:param asynchronous: Whether the job is to be run asynchronously. For now this\n\n> only applies to jobs that are scheduled to run locally.\n\n```\ntype asynchronous\n\nbool\n\nparam save\n\nWhether the documented should be saved to the database.\n\ntype save\n\nbool\n\nparam parentJob\n\nThe job which will be set as a parent\n\ntype parentJob\n\nJob\n\nparam otherFields\n\nAny additional fields to set on the job.\n\ntype otherFields\n\ndict\n```\n"]}, {"name": "girder_jobs.models.job.Job.save", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "job", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["We extend save so that we can serialize the kwargs before sending them\nto the database. This will allow kwargs with $ and . characters in the\nkeys."]}, {"name": "girder_jobs.models.job.Job.find", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Overrides the default find behavior to exclude the log by default.\n\n```\nparam includeLog\n\nWhether to include the log field in the documents.\n\ntype includeLog\n\nbool\n```\n"]}, {"name": "girder_jobs.models.job.Job.load", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["We extend load to deserialize the kwargs back into a dict since we\nserialized them on the way into the database.\n\n```\nparam includeLog\n\nWhether to include the log field in the document.\n\ntype includeLog\n\nbool\n```\n"]}, {"name": "girder_jobs.models.job.Job.scheduleJob", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "job", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Trigger the event to schedule this job. Other plugins are in charge of\nactually scheduling and/or executing the job, except in the case when\nthe handler is 'local'."]}, {"name": "girder_jobs.models.job.Job.createJobToken", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "job", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "days", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create a token that can be used just for the management of an individual\njob, e.g. updating job info, progress, logs, status."]}, {"name": "girder_jobs.models.job.Job.updateJob", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "job", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "log", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "overwrite", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "status", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "progressTotal", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "progressCurrent", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "notify", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "progressMessage", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "otherFields", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Update an existing job. Any of the updateable fields that are set to None in the kwargs of\nthis method will not be modified. If you set progress information on the job for the first\ntime and set notify=True, a new notification record for the job progress will be created.\nIf notify=True, job status changes will also create a notification with type=\"job_status\",\nand log changes will create a notification with type=\"job_log\".\n\n```\nparam job\n\nThe job document to update.\n\nparam log\n\nMessage to append to the job log. If you wish to overwrite\ninstead of append, pass overwrite=True.\n\ntype log\n\nstr\n\nparam overwrite\n\nWhether to overwrite the log (default is append).\n\ntype overwrite\n\nbool\n\nparam status\n\nNew status for the job.\n\ntype status\n\nJobStatus\n\nparam progressTotal\n\nMax progress value for this job.\n\nparam otherFields\n\nAny additional fields to set on the job.\n\ntype otherFields\n\ndict\n```\n"]}, {"name": "girder_jobs.models.job.Job._updateLog", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "job", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "log", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "overwrite", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "now", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "notify", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "user", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "updates", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Helper for updating a job's log."]}, {"name": "girder_jobs.models.job.Job._createUpdateStatusNotification", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "now", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "user", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "job", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "girder_jobs.models.job.Job._updateStatus", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "job", "type": null, "d